The paper deals with object recognition in remote sensing imagery using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning the alignment of multisource data and the classification model in a unified framework, which is a task that can be achieved using machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms to improve the classification accuracy, which is a topic that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
